fields.description: The list of Availability zones to use for nodes. This can only be specified if the AgentPoolType property is 'VirtualMachineScaleSets'.
fields.name: AvailabilityZones

fields.description: AKS will associate the specified agent pool with the Capacity Reservation Group.
fields.name: CapacityReservationGroupID

fields.description: Number of agents (VMs) to host docker containers. Allowed values must be in the range of 0 to 1000 (inclusive) for user pools and in the range of 1 to 1000 (inclusive) for system pools. The default value is 1.
fields.name: Count

fields.description: CreationData to be used to specify the source Snapshot ID if the node pool will be created/upgraded using a snapshot.
fields.name: CreationData

fields.description: If orchestratorVersion was a fully specified version <major.minor.patch>, this field will be exactly equal to it. If orchestratorVersion was <major.minor>, this field will contain the full <major.minor.patch> version being used.
fields.name: CurrentOrchestratorVersion

fields.description: Whether to enable auto-scaler
fields.name: EnableAutoScaling

fields.description: When set to true, AKS adds a label to the node indicating that the feature is enabled and deploys a daemonset along with host services to sync custom certificate authorities from user-provided list of base64 encoded certificates into node trust stores. Defaults to false.
fields.name: EnableCustomCATrust

fields.description: This is only supported on certain VM sizes and in certain Azure regions. For more information, see: https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/aks/enable-host-encryption
fields.name: EnableEncryptionAtHost

fields.description: See [Add a FIPS-enabled node pool](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/aks/use-multiple-node-pools#add-a-fips-enabled-node-pool-preview) for more details.
fields.name: EnableFIPS

fields.description: Some scenarios may require nodes in a node pool to receive their own dedicated public IP addresses. A common scenario is for gaming workloads, where a console needs to make a direct connection to a cloud virtual machine to minimize hops. For more information see [assigning a public IP per node](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/aks/use-multiple-node-pools#assign-a-public-ip-per-node-for-your-node-pools). The default is false.
fields.name: EnableNodePublicIP

fields.description: Whether to enable UltraSSD
fields.name: EnableUltraSSD

fields.description: GPUInstanceProfile to be used to specify GPU MIG instance profile for supported GPU VM SKU.
fields.name: GpuInstanceProfile

fields.description: This is of the form: /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Compute/hostGroups/{hostGroupName}. For more information see [Azure dedicated hosts](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/virtual-machines/dedicated-hosts).
fields.name: HostGroupID

fields.description: The Kubelet configuration on the agent pool nodes.
fields.name: KubeletConfig

fields.description: The OS configuration of Linux agent nodes.
fields.name: LinuxOSConfig

fields.description: The maximum number of nodes for auto-scaling
fields.name: MaxCount

fields.description: The maximum number of pods that can run on a node.
fields.name: MaxPods

fields.description: A base64-encoded string which will be written to /etc/motd after decoding. This allows customization of the message of the day for Linux nodes. It must not be specified for Windows nodes. It must be a static string (i.e., will be printed raw and not be executed as a script).
fields.name: MessageOfTheDay

fields.description: The minimum number of nodes for auto-scaling
fields.name: MinCount

fields.description: Windows agent pool names must be 6 characters or less.
fields.name: Name

fields.description: Network-related settings of an agent pool.
fields.name: NetworkProfile

fields.description: The version of node image
fields.name: NodeImageVersion

fields.description: The node labels to be persisted across all nodes in agent pool.
fields.name: NodeLabels

fields.description: This is of the form: /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Network/publicIPPrefixes/{publicIPPrefixName}
fields.name: NodePublicIPPrefixID

fields.description: The taints added to new nodes during node pool create and scale. For example, key=value:NoSchedule.
fields.name: NodeTaints

fields.description: Both patch version <major.minor.patch> and <major.minor> are supported. When <major.minor> is specified, the latest supported patch version is chosen automatically. Updating the agent pool with the same <major.minor> once it has been created will not trigger an upgrade, even if a newer patch version is available. As a best practice, you should upgrade all node pools in an AKS cluster to the same Kubernetes version. The node pool version must have the same major version as the control plane. The node pool minor version must be within two minor versions of the control plane version. The node pool version cannot be greater than the control plane version. For more information see [upgrading a node pool](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/aks/use-multiple-node-pools#upgrade-a-node-pool).
fields.name: OrchestratorVersion

fields.description: If omitted, pod IPs are statically assigned on the node subnet (see vnetSubnetID for more details). This is of the form: /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Network/virtualNetworks/{virtualNetworkName}/subnets/{subnetName}
fields.name: PodSubnetID

fields.description: When an Agent Pool is first created it is initially Running. The Agent Pool can be stopped by setting this field to Stopped. A stopped Agent Pool stops all of its VMs and does not accrue billing charges. An Agent Pool can only be stopped if it is Running and provisioning state is Succeeded
fields.name: PowerState

fields.description: The current deployment or provisioning state.
fields.name: ProvisioningState

fields.description: The ID for Proximity Placement Group.
fields.name: ProximityPlacementGroupID

fields.description: This also effects the cluster autoscaler behavior. If not specified, it defaults to Delete.
fields.name: ScaleDownMode

fields.description: This cannot be specified unless the scaleSetPriority is 'Spot'. If not specified, the default is 'Delete'.
fields.name: ScaleSetEvictionPolicy

fields.description: The Virtual Machine Scale Set priority. If not specified, the default is 'Regular'.
fields.name: ScaleSetPriority

fields.description: Possible values are any decimal value greater than zero or -1 which indicates the willingness to pay any on-demand price. For more details on spot pricing, see [spot VMs pricing](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/virtual-machines/spot-vms#pricing)
fields.name: SpotMaxPrice

fields.description: The tags to be persisted on the agent pool virtual machine scale set.
fields.name: Tags

fields.description: Settings for upgrading the agentpool
fields.name: UpgradeSettings

fields.description: VM size availability varies by region. If a node contains insufficient compute resources (memory, cpu, etc) pods might fail to run correctly. For more details on restricted VM sizes, see: https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/aks/quotas-skus-regions
fields.name: VMSize

fields.description: If this is not specified, a VNET and subnet will be generated and used. If no podSubnetID is specified, this applies to nodes and pods, otherwise it applies to just nodes. This is of the form: /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Network/virtualNetworks/{virtualNetworkName}/subnets/{subnetName}
fields.name: VnetSubnetID

fields.description: The Windows agent pool's specific profile.
fields.name: WindowsProfile
